<subSubSection id="66C5058FFFCEFF990790FB5F13C689AD" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2E605604FFCEFF990790FB5F12C688AA" blockId="19.[143,1104,1193,1479]" box="[143,251,1193,1216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">
<heading id="7528E168FFCEFF990790FB5F12C688AA" box="[143,251,1193,1216]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCEFF990790FB5F12C688AA" box="[143,251,1193,1216]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFCEFF990790FB2613C689AD" blockId="19.[143,1104,1193,1479]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCEFF990611FB27136F8882" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" box="[270,338,1232,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sesieutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhui" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCEFF990611FB27136F8882" box="[270,338,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">J. zhui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCEFF990647FB2613EC888D" box="[344,465,1232,1256]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCEFF990449FB27163B8882" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[854,1030,1232,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCEFF990449FB27163B8882" box="[854,1030,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">J. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCEFF990314FB261282896D" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by their smaller copulatory orifices that are located more anteriorly, internal ducts that are simple, and the spermathecae that are robust. In 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCEFF990404FAE611F08942" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[795,973,1296,1320]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCEFF990404FAE611F08942" box="[795,973,1296,1320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">J. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCEFF9904CAFAF9166D894D" box="[981,1104,1295,1319]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the copulatory orifices are distinctly larger and medially situated on the epigynal plate (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCEFF990788FAB91332890D" box="[151,271,1359,1383]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="13.[143,210,790,812]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,169,757]" captionTargetId="figure-5@13.[145,1102,169,758]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 7. Jacaena spp. Epigynal region, ventral (A–F). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (A); J. punctata sp. nov., paratype (B); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (C); J. mihun (D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. peculiaris sp. nov., holotype (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517662/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">Figure 7A</figureCitation>
), the internal ducts are partially enlarged, and the anterior portion of the spermathecae is spherical (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCEFF9906A9FA99101589ED" box="[438,552,1391,1415]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">Figure 8F</figureCitation>
). Males differ by the apex of the conductor, which is blunt, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCEFF99066DFA66101E89CD" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[370,547,1423,1447]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCEFF99066DFA66101E89CD" box="[370,547,1423,1447]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">J. schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCEFF990534FA79109B89CD" box="[555,678,1423,1447]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the conductor is sharply pointed and more elongate (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCEFF990622FA59138389AD" box="[317,446,1455,1479]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[211,278,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (originally misidentified as Sesieutes schwendingeri) (D–F); J. mihun, holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517648/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">Figures 4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCEFF9906D6FA5913D389AD" box="[457,494,1455,1479]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="17.[143,210,924,946]" captionTargetBox="[146,1102,170,891]" captionTargetId="figure-5@17.[145,1102,169,891]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 9. Jacaena spp. Distal part of male palp, ventral, showing conductor, tip of embolus and tegular apophysis (A, D). Ditto, retrolateral (B). Ditto, prolateral (C, E). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. lunulata sp. nov., holotype (D, E). C, conductor. E, embolus. TA, tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517666/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1556">9A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
